The management of the Benue State Universal Basic Education Board (SUBEB) has suspended its Accounts Clerk in charge of Teachers Payroll, Lawrence Makir, over alleged inclusion of some teachers’ names on the payroll. Acting Chairman of SUBEB, Mnyam Matthew, ordered the suspension of the account clerk after it was allegedly discovered that he re-instated some teachers who were earlier removed from the payroll by the board’s screening committee without management’s consent. In a statement made available to our correspondent in Makurdi, yesterday by the SUBEB Head of Information and Protocol, Sar Erdoo, the chairman noted that the action taken was to enable the board carry out a thorough investigation before a final decision is taken. The SUBEB boss further reiterated his resolve not to condone corrupt practices from any staff, stressing that the verification committee in which he doubles as the chairman would come out with the actual number of teachers in the Basic Education sub-sector of Benue State. Matthew, also in the statement disclosed the removal a former permanent member of the board, Moses Enenche, as member of the Benue SUBEB Teachers Screening and Verification Committee.  Benue: SUBEB suspends clerk over names inclusion in payroll Inside the massive fraud in Kogi Councils ‘SUBEB is the problem of basic education in Kogi’ Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin